financial crisis inquiry commission announces release date for final report page 1 media advisory for immediate release media inquiries january 19 2011 tucker warren 202 292 1346 twarren fcic gov financial crisis inquiry commission announces release date for final report washington dc the financial crisis inquiry commission will release its report on the causes of the financial crisis to the president congress and the american people on the morning of thursday january 27 2011 in washington dc additional details will be announced closer to the date of release in the course of its research and investigation the commission reviewed millions of pages of documents interviewed more than 700 witnesses and held 19 days of public hearings in new york washington dc and communities across the country that were hit hard by the crisis the report will include the results of the commission's inquiry and the commission's conclusions as to the causes of the financial crisis based on this inquiry for more visit fcic gov
